{{year-header}}
==January==
* '''[[20 January|20]]''' - [[Vincent Trought]], a member of the [[T.C.B.S.]], dies. He had been severely ill since the autumn.
==April==
* '''[[5 April|5]]''' -  [[John Le Mesurier]], who would voice [[Bilbo Baggins|Bilbo]] in the [[The Lord of the Rings (1981 radio series)|1981 radio adaptation of ''The Lord of the Rings'']], is born. 
==May==
* '''[[18 May|18]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] [[:File:Oxford Union Society Library ledger - Tolkien 1912 fee.jpg|pays his Oxford Union Library fees]].
* '''[[31 May|31]]''' - German translator [[Margaret Carroux]] is born.
==July==
* '''[[17 July|17]]''' - Author [[Barbara Strachey]] is born.
==December==
* '''?''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] creates the illustration ''[[End of the World]]''.
==Unknown==
*The [[Apolausticks]] are founded at [[Oxford]].
